TFc3p-zMVfAH0StbnnOINvU94H82l_3xOn2okSYRyrG560zcQWvglFIVIqnpg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test organization**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to handle the tests for the active class. It seems like there should be a dedicated file for that instead of editing the outer file, which would create some issues. Should I undo the changes, or is it better to create a new file for the anonymous class while keeping the original? Moving the new test to this new file sounds like the best approach, especially since the existing file can remain for the original outer structure.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Organizing test classes**\\n\\nI'm considering whether I need to remove the outer class or not. I think it's fine to keep it, but I need to create a new test in a dedicated class called \\\"active.\\\" So, I'll edit the existing imports and tests, and create a new file. This way, we'll have coverage for \\\"active\\\" while still registering in the outer class. It looks like I'll need to revert the imports in the existing file and remove the new test as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_H8e0tb8NXuzUSY0z3KEA76Pg|fc_08f23d53e5f86dbc016a0f3af7fd408196a858d71910a9d1f4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/OrgApacheKafkaCommonUtilsLoggingSignalHandlerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import org.apache.kafka.common.utils.LoggingSignalHandler;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport sun.misc.Signal;\nimport sun.misc.SignalHandler;\n\nimport java.util.LinkedHashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.concurrent.CountDownLatch;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\n", "newText": "import org.apache.kafka.common.utils.LoggingSignalHandler;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void registersLoggingSignalHandlers() {\n        assertThatCode(() -> new LoggingSignalHandler().register())\n                .doesNotThrowAnyException();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void delegatesRaisedSignalToPreviousSignalHandler() throws Exception {\n        CountDownLatch previousHandlerInvoked = new CountDownLatch(1);\n        Map<Signal, SignalHandler> originalHandlers = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n        Signal hup = new Signal(\"HUP\");\n\n        try {\n            for (String signalName : new String[] {\"TERM\", \"INT\", \"HUP\"}) {\n                Signal signal = new Signal(signalName);\n                SignalHandler previousHandler = Signal.handle(signal, handledSignal -> {\n                    if (\"HUP\".equals(handledSignal.getName())) {\n                        previousHandlerInvoked.countDown();\n                    }\n                });\n                originalHandlers.put(signal, previousHandler);\n            }\n\n            new LoggingSignalHandler().register();\n            Signal.raise(hup);\n\n            assertThat(previousHandlerInvoked.await(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS)).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            for (Map.Entry<Signal, SignalHandler> originalHandler : originalHandlers.entrySet()) {\n                Signal.handle(originalHandler.getKey(), originalHandler.getValue());\n            }\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void registersLoggingSignalHandlers() {\n        assertThatCode(() -> new LoggingSignalHandler().register())\n                .doesNotThrowAnyException();\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1362, "output": 1638, "cacheRead": 15872, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18872, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779383010539, "responseId": "resp_08f23d53e5f86dbc016a0f3ae2e3688196b61a293087a31